Autonomous Startup Multi-Agent System - Rapid Prototype Plan

 Executive Summary

 Build a simulation-based prototype of an autonomous startup multi-agent system in hours/days that demonstrates:
 - Hierarchical multi-agent coordination (Planner → Actor agents)
 - Build-Measure-Learn cycle execution
 - Memory systems (semantic, episodic, procedural)
 - Simulated ecosystem (startups, VCs, platform agents)

 Key Strategy: Simulate rather than build. Use mocks and simplified implementations to demonstrate architecture and coordination patterns.

 Revised Technology Stack (Rapid Prototype)

 Core: Python 3.11+ with Minimal Dependencies

 Agent Framework: LangGraph (lightweight setup)
 - Fastest path to multi-agent coordination
 - Built-in state management
 - Can mock LLM calls for speed/cost

 LLM Strategy: Hybrid
 - Primary: Anthropic Claude Haiku (fast + cheap for prototyping)
 - Fallback: OpenAI GPT-4o-mini
 - Simulation Mode: Mock responses (pre-scripted for deterministic testing)

 Data Storage: Simplified
 - Structured Data: SQLite (zero setup, file-based)
 - Vector Storage: In-memory dictionaries with cosine similarity (no separate DB needed)
 - Cache: Python dictionaries (no Redis for prototype)

 No Heavy Infrastructure:
 - ❌ Skip Temporal.io (too complex for prototype)
 - ❌ Skip Airflow (use simple Python schedulers)
 - ❌ Skip Docker/Kubernetes (local execution only)
 - ❌ Skip FastAPI (use simple CLI or Streamlit UI)

