 Notes

 - Mock Mode: Set MOCK_MODE=true in .env to use pre-scripted LLM responses. This makes the simulation deterministic and free (no API costs). Set to false to use real LLM calls for more realistic agent behavior.
 - Seed Data: The simulation uses 50 simulated startups and 30 simulated VCs in data/seed/. Customize these JSON files to test different scenarios.
 - Extensibility: The architecture is designed to easily swap mock implementations for real ones. Each component (memory, LLM, agents) has a clear interface that can be upgraded incrementally.
 - Learning Curve: The prototype demonstrates learning across 3 iterations. In a production system, this would happen over weeks/months with real data.